1512:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    (+) Before calling any tamper or internal tamper function, you have to call first
1513:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****        HAL_RTC_Init() function.
1514:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    (+) In that ine you can select to output tamper event on RTC pin.
1515:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
1516:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    (+) Enable the Tamper and configure the Tamper filter count, trigger Edge
1517:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****        or Level according to the Tamper filter (if equal to 0 Edge else Level)
1518:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****        value, sampling frequency, NoErase, MaskFlag, precharge or discharge and
1519:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****        Pull-UP, timestamp using the HAL_RTCEx_SetTamper() function.
1520:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****        You can configure Tamper with interrupt mode using HAL_RTCEx_SetTamper_IT() function.
1521:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    (+) The default configuration of the Tamper erases the backup registers. To avoid
1522:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****        erase, enable the NoErase field on the TAMP_TAMPCR register.
1523:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
1524:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    (+) Enable Internal Tamper and configure it with interrupt, timestamp using
1525:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****        the HAL_RTCEx_SetInternalTamper() function.
